    <h1 class="center-spacing">Best Practices</h1>

    <p class="justify-content xlarge-text-size input-field-text">Each OKR time period lasts 3 months and consists of 3 Objectives. This gives you quarterly chunks to focus on your Mind (Objective 1), Body (Objective 2), & Soul (Objective 3). Try to pick objectives that keep you balanced and well-rounded for longevity.</p>
    <p class="justify-content xlarge-text-size input-field-text">OKR statements should be kept within a sentence or two to maintain clarity and avoid ambiguity. While there isn't a fixed character limit, it's important to prioritize clarity and simplicity.</p>
    <p class="justify-content xlarge-text-size input-field-text">The goal is to set large challenging objectives, like a <a class="purple-font" href="https://asana.com/resources/bhag-big-hairy-audacious-goal" target="_blank">Big Hairy Audacious Goal (BHAG)</a>. This means it isn't easy to achieve, and you give yourself a challenge to work towards. <i class="input-field-text">i.e. Goal is 5 and you achieve 3 vs. Goal is 100 and you achieve 50... 50 items accomplished is greater than only 3 items</i></p>
